Visiting argentina Prof Caamano
To Give Piano Concert Saturday
roberts Caamano, argentina
composer and spanish, will present a public concert tomorrow
at 8 p.m. in Roberts Theatre.
C amino, britney -copyright
his ng professor of music at
Grinnell this semester, will
p e r fo r m piano works by
Mozart, Beethoven, C h o p in
Brahms, a n d
I) e b u ss y, as
well as one of
his own competitions.
Born in Bus:not A i r e s in
1923, Caamano
has had an impressive career
as spanish, composer, and educated, w e i la
known in Solid)
America, t h is
United States,
and Europe.
In 1952 he
represented the
argentina at the
I n t e r n eternal Arts Program in New
York City, in
1958 he was invited 'to p effort his own
concerts to r
Piano and Orchestra at the
First Inter-American Music
Festival in Washington, DC,
and also in 1958 he received the
best instrumentation’s award
from the Music Critics’ Assor
station of Argentina. Last October he performed his piano
concerts at the First Music
Festival of America and Spain,
held in Madrid.
Among numerous works he
_has been commissioner to com»
pose is his recent printer for
Piano and Strings, 0p. 25, for
the Elizabeth Sprague Coolidge
Foundation in 1962. His works
have been performed by major
orchestras and artists in the
United States and Europe as
roberts Cnumono
well as South America and
have received several significant artistic awards.
He is on the faculty of two
musical institutions, the National conservation of Buenus
tires and the Pontifical catholic University of Buenos tires.
From 1960 to 1964 he was artistic director of the Colon Theatre, one of the world’s most
distinguished opera institutions.
 
